.TH "ubi_open_volume_path" 9 "ubi_open_volume_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_open_volume_path \- open UBI volume by its character device node path.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ubi_volume_desc *" ubi_open_volume_path
.BI "(const char *pathname "  ","
.BI "int mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pathname" 12
volume character device node path
.IP "mode" 12
open mode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is similar to '\fBubi_open_volume\fP', but opens a volume the path
to its character device node.
